<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6050&amp;p=56603#p56603"><![CDATA[
Lets say I got a drum sample, ripped from a game. Unfortunately it's too quiet and it ain't noticeable in the mixdown. I thought of editing the DPCM file with a hex-editor, but I don't know which hex values affect the volume. (I'm using Hex Workshop Trial) I tried using AND command to increase all values (by 1) but the result obviously wasn't satisfying.<br /><br />I use Famitracker and yes, I also use the Zxx effect on those.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3763">Eightbit Allstar</a> — Sun Feb 14, 2010 12:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
